          <p>My personal philosophy as a designer is to seek a deep understanding of each client, the problem they are solving, and the culture of its users; much like a method actor when they are developing a character for a movie. It's my responsibility to empathize with the user while also balancing the needs of stakeholders in every project.  My passion for knowledge and growth have led me to explore the full breadth of design tools and languages which I consider my greatest strength as a designer. As new problem-solving tools and technologies advance, I don't expect to ever "arrive"; but the more I grasp, the more challenging the problems I can tackle to better serve a diverse client base.</p>
